briefTitle: Evaluation of the Immune Responses of GSK Biologicals' HPV Vaccine Following Manufacturing Process Adaptation.
officialTitle: Assess Lot-to-lot Consistency of GSK Biologicals' HPV-16/18 L1/AS04 Vaccine Following Manufacturing Adjustments Administered Intramuscularly According to a 0,1,6-mth Schedule in Healthy Female Subjects (18-25 y)
summary: Human papillomavirus infection has clearly been recognized as the cause of cervical cancer. Indeed, the infection of the cervix by certain oncogenic types of HPV, if not cleared , can lead over time to cervical cancer in women . This study will compare the immune response induced by different lots of the HPV-16/18 L1/AS04 vaccine, following adjustments to the manufacturing process.

primaryOutcome.measure: Number of Seroconverted (SCR) Subjects for Anti-Human Papillomavirus Type 16 (Anti-HPV-16) and Anti-Human Papillomavirus Type 18 (Anti-HPV-18)
